newsitem.title: CANADA: Canadian West Coast Vessel Loadings - CWB.
newsitem.headline: Canadian West Coast Vessel Loadings - CWB.

text.p: Canadian Wheat Board reported three ships loading, 14 waiting and six due at the Canadian West Coast, as of Tuesday.

The longest wait to load on the West Coast was 19 days. Five ships loaded in Thunder Bay, three waited and nine were due. Two ships loaded on the East Coast, two waited to load up to nine days and 17 were due.
